import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['open'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Opening Prices')
    plt.axvline(data['open'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['open'].median():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Opening Prices')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of opening prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    data['volume'] = data['volume'].astype(float)
    avg_daily_volume = data['volume'].mean()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    plt.bar(data['date'], data['volume'], color='blue', label='Daily Volume')
    plt.axhline(avg_daily_volume, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Daily Volume: {avg_daily_volume:.2f}')
    
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Volume Traded')
    plt.title('What is the average daily volume traded?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['close'], data['volume'], c=data['volume'], cmap='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Closing Prices')
    plt.ylabel('Volume Traded')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between closing prices and volume traded?', wrap=True)
    
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="Volume Traded")
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
